main event: A white, irregularly-shaped object was observed moving erratically at high speed and disappearing in Wales, Alaska.
interesting points: The object appeared like a star at first, then became larger and irregular in shape.
The object moved erratically at high speed and disappeared.
There were no radar blips detected at the time of the sighting, indicating it was an unusual visual observation.
The sighting was reported by Lt. Hanscom from the Dover Radar Lab.
The report concludes that there is insufficient information to draw a definitive conclusion.
